text.tspan: 1. **Pull-Based Model**: Each operator implements the PhysicalOp trait
2. **Lazy Execution**: Root (Projection) drives execution by calling next()
3. **Pipeline Flow**: Data flows upward as operators pull from children
4. **Memory Efficient**: Only processes what's needed, when needed
5. **Natural Backpressure**: No operator produces more than parent consumes

g.text: open(&mut self, context: &QueryContext) -> Result<()> next(&mut self) -> Result<Option<Row>> close(&mut self) -> Result<()>
